Rolf Harris faced a flood of fresh abuse allegations yesterday as his victims vowed to reduce him to ruin by launching claims on his £11million fortune.

A dozen new alleged victims have contacted lawyers seeking compensation payouts which could top £70,000 each, with a High Court civil claim set to be launched in weeks which will effectively freeze the disgraced entertainer’s assets.

Harris, 84, faces being stripped of his fortune and honours, while galleries, schools and even a zoo scrambled to remove all trace of the paintings and plaques which once celebrated his life’s work.  

