Yesterday plaques honouring the paedophile were torn down at Colchester Zoo in Essex where Harris opened a £1million elephant enclosure in 1997. Paintings were also removed from schools and galleries in Australia.

Yesterday a law firm said it had been contacted by 12 women thought to be from the UK, New Zealand and Australia.

Their allegations of sexual abuse could be passed to Scotland Yard, which is already reviewing a handful of new victims.

